Huawei recently launched its new Mate 20 Pro high-end smartphone, and the device is now available in South Africa. The Huawei Mate 20 Pro can be purchased outright or taken out on a contract from mobile operators, with major networks now listing their contract pricing. Users can purchase the Mate 20 Pro with 128GB internal storage and 6GB RAM from various retailers for a recommended price of R18,999. Currently Vodacom, MTN, and Telkomâ€™s websites all feature contract pricing for the Huawei Mate 20 Pro, while Cell C has not yet added any postpaid pricing for the new device. MTN currently only offers the device on its Made for Me S plan, and has bundled a once-off 14GB Entertainment Pass valid for 30 days with this contract. We compared the best contract deals for the Huawei Mate 20 Pro from local operators below. Vodacom offers the Mate 20 Pro on a number of contracts, including its uChoose, Smart, and Red plans. The device is available on contract from R799 per month.  MTN offers the Huawei Mate 20 Pro on a single contract plan with a bundled 14GB Entertainment Pass. The device is available on Made for Me S from R799 per month.  Telkom offers the Huawei Mate 20 Pro on all of its FreeMe postpaid plans. FreeMe plans include a number of extras, such as LIT music and video streaming and free Telkom-to-Telkom calls. The Huawei Mate 20 Pro is available from R699 per month. 